# Emitter Module
#
# Output formatters for the unified reporting system.
# Provides multiple output formats for different use cases:
# - **Human**: Colorful terminal output with source context
# - **JSON**: Machine-readable JSON for tooling
# - **SARIF**: Static Analysis Results Interchange Format
# - **LSP**: Language Server Protocol diagnostics
#
# # Quick Start
#
# ```simple
# import std.report.emitter
#
# # Human-readable output
# val human = HumanEmitter.default_emitter()
# human.add_source("main.spl", source_code)
# print human.emit(report)
#
# # JSON output
# val json = JsonEmitter.pretty()
# print json.emit_all(reports)
#
# # SARIF output (for CI tools)
# val sarif = SarifEmitter.default_emitter()
# print sarif.emit(reports)
#
# # LSP diagnostics (for IDEs)
# val lsp = LspEmitter.default_emitter()
# print lsp.emit_publish_diagnostics(uri, reports)
# ```
#
# # Output Formats
#
# | Format | Use Case | Features |
# |--------|----------|----------|
# | Human | Terminal | Colors, source context, underlines |
# | JSON | Tooling | Structured, machine-readable |
# | SARIF | CI/CD | Standard format, fixes included |
# | LSP | IDEs | Real-time diagnostics, code actions |
#
# # Human Output Features
#
# - ANSI color codes (configurable)
# - Source code context with line numbers
# - Underlines for error locations
# - Notes, help, and suggestions
# - Summary with error/warning counts
#
# # JSON Output Features
#
# - Pretty or compact format
# - Source snippets (optional)
# - Newline-delimited JSON (NDJSON) for streaming
#
# # SARIF Output Features
#
# - SARIF v2.1.0 compliant
# - Rule definitions
# - Fix suggestions as SARIF fixes
# - Related locations
#
# # LSP Output Features
#
# - LSP 3.17 compatible
# - Diagnostic severities and tags
# - Code actions (quick fixes)
# - Publish diagnostics notifications

